oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Canary Calendar: "WAIT 'TIL NEXT YEAR!"
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Nierenberg, Charlotte
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The old Dodger cry seems particularlyopportune at this time of the year whencanary breeders and their birds definitelyneed and deserve a rest!If a pair of canaries has raised two successful clutches, it is sometimes a temptationto allow a third. However, since thebreeding cycle takes its toll (especiallyon first-year birds) a third nest should bediscouraged. If a previous try resulted inclear or unhatched eggs, the pair may bepermitted to try again.
